      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM STEALTHY NZ (4) came from this barrier and worked to the front before going on to score by 8 metres when resuming at Pinjarra. That took his record to three from five. Fitter and has upside so can go through his grades. IN RARE AIR NZ (8) has not raced since he finished 3.8 metres away in fourth here three-and-a-half months ago. That was his only time out of the placings in a seven-start maiden campaign. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but looking for a good return. JUSTASMOOTH MIKI (1) is a player having come from this barrier to place in both starts to date. THE FINAL OFFER NZ (7) showed some ability as a juvenile, highlighted by a win at this circuit and distance. Must be respected first up.",
